# Auth Token Implementation Plan (Next.js Frontend)

Backend is unchanged. Frontend is done. Only token management is pending.
Mirrors the Electron app's architecture using `localStorage` instead of `electron-store`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> All `localStorage` access must be guarded with `typeof window !== "undefined"` to avoid SSR errors in Next.js.

---

## Backend Contracts (Unchanged)

| Method | Endpoint | Auth | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/api/auth/magic-link` | ❌ | Send OTP email |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/oauth/google` | ❌ | Get Google OAuth redirect URL |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/refresh` | ❌ | Body: `{ refreshToken }` → returns `{ data: { access_token, refresh_token, expires_in } }` |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/logout` | ❌ | Body: `{ refreshToken, userId }` — always succeeds |
| `GET` | `/api/auth/verify` | ✅ Bearer | Returns `{ data: { userId, email } }` |

Supabase redirects to `https://yoursite.com/auth/success#access_token=...&refresh_token=...&expires_in=...` after login.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Component 1 — Token Storage

#### [NEW] `lib/tokenStore.ts`

Thin `localStorage` wrapper. Typed getters/setters for:
- [getTokenStore() / setTokenStore(store | null)](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/cache.service.ts#32-35) — the full `{ accessToken, refreshToken, tokenExpiresAt, expiresIn }` object stored under key `"tokenStore"`
- [getUser() / setUser(user | null)](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/cache.service.ts#24-27) — stored under key `"user"`
- `clearAll()` — wipes both keys

---

### Component 2 — HTTP Client

#### [NEW] `lib/apiService.ts`  — class [BackendAPIService](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/api.service.ts#46-1351)

**Private `request<T>(endpoint, options, skipAuth?)`:**
1. Reads `accessToken` from `tokenStore` → injects `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.
2. On `401` → calls [refreshAccessToken()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/api.service.ts#233-281) → retries the request **once** with new token.
3. If refresh also fails → calls `tokenStore.clearAll()` → redirects to `/login`.
4. Uses an `isRefreshing` flag + queue to prevent simultaneous refresh races.

**Key public methods:**
- [refreshAccessToken(): Promise<boolean>](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/api.service.ts#233-281) — POSTs to `/api/auth/refresh`, saves new tokens via `tokenStore.setTokenStore(...)`
- [verifyToken()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/api.service.ts#332-335) — GETs `/api/auth/verify`
- [logout()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/api.service.ts#304-331) — POSTs to `/api/auth/logout` (skipAuth), then `tokenStore.clearAll()`
- [getUserProfile()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/api.service.ts#342-345) — GETs user profile
- *(All other app API methods go here too)*

---

### Component 3 — Auth Orchestrator

#### [NEW] `lib/authService.ts`

**[initialize()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/backend/src/server.ts#50-77)** — called once on app load:
1. Read `tokenStore` + `user` from localStorage.
2. If both exist → call [refreshAccessToken()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/api.service.ts#233-281) eagerly.
3. If refresh succeeds → [scheduleTokenRefresh()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/auth.service.ts#137-182) → return user as authenticated.
4. If refresh fails (network error) → keep cached session, retry later.
5. If refresh fails (invalid token) → `clearAll()` → return unauthenticated.
6. If nothing in storage → return unauthenticated.

**[handleOAuthCallback(url: string)](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/auth.service.ts#375-428)** — called on `/auth/success` page mount:
1. Parse `#access_token`, `#refresh_token`, `#expires_in` from URL hash.
2. Save to `tokenStore`.
3. Call [verifyToken()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/api.service.ts#332-335) → fetch user profile → save user to `tokenStore`.
4. Redirect to `/explore` (or intended destination).

**[signOut()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/backend/src/services/auth.service.ts#112-139):**
1. Call `apiService.logout()` (best-effort).
2. `tokenStore.clearAll()`.
3. Redirect to `/login`.

**[scheduleTokenRefresh()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/auth.service.ts#137-182)** — proactive cron:
- `setInterval` every 60 seconds.
- If `tokenExpiresAt - Date.now() < 5 * 60 * 1000` → call [refreshAccessToken()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/src/main/services/api.service.ts#233-281).
- Store interval ID → `clearInterval` on sign-out.

---

### Component 4 — Auth Context

#### [NEW] `context/AuthContext.tsx`

Provides `{ user, isAuthenticated, isLoading }` to the component tree.

- On mount: calls `authService.initialize()` → updates state.
- Exposes: [signOut()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/backend/src/services/auth.service.ts#112-139), [signInWithMagicLink(email)](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/backend/src/services/auth.service.ts#19-47), [signInWithGoogle()](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Invook/backend/src/services/auth.service.ts#80-111).
- Wraps the app in `_app.tsx` or `layout.tsx`.

---

### Component 5 — OAuth Callback Page

#### [NEW] `app/auth/success/page.tsx`

- Client Component (`"use client"`).
- On mount (`useEffect`): calls `authService.handleOAuthCallback(window.location.href)`.
- Shows a loading spinner while tokens are processed.
- Redirects happen inside `authService` — this page just renders a loader.

---

## Verification Plan

1. Visit `/explore` unauthenticated → public items load, no token in localStorage.
2. Log in via Magic Link / Google → redirected to `/auth/success` → tokens stored in localStorage → redirected to app.
3. Make any authenticated request → `Authorization: Bearer` header sent automatically.
4. Wait for token to near expiry → proactive refresh fires → new tokens stored.
5. Simulate expired token → `401` triggers refresh → request retried with new token → succeeds.
6. Log out → localStorage cleared → redirected to `/login`.
7. After logout, revisit app → unauthenticated state shown.
